# Synthetic CRM Data Generator

## Quick Start

```bash
cd lead-scoring-poc
python scripts/generate_data.py
# Output: data/raw/accounts.csv, leads.csv, contacts.csv, campaign_members.csv
```

## Configuration

```python
NUM_ACCOUNTS = 200
NUM_LEADS = 600
NUM_CONTACTS = 400
NUM_CAMPAIGN_MEMBERS = 4000
```

## Salesforce Object Model

```
Account (1) ←── (N) Contact
                       ↑
Lead ──── converts to ─┘
Campaign (1) ←── (N) CampaignMember ──→ Lead OR Contact
```

## Injected DQ Patterns

- DQ-1: Broken conversion links (~20% of converted)
- DQ-2: Email duplication (~8% of leads)
- DQ-4: ETL timestamp clustering (~80% of leads)
- DQ-6: Non-prospect contamination (~13%)
- DQ-8: Automation-inflated engagement (~60% of emails)

## Engagement Distribution

Zipf distribution (power law): most entities 1-3 memberships, some 10-20, outliers 30-50.

## Required Test Personas (Appendix B)

| # | Persona | Expected |
|---|---------|----------|
| 1 | VP Security, named account, 3 recent webinars | Hot |
| 2 | Same profile, all engagement >6mo old | Mid/Low |
| 3 | Junior analyst, 15 responses in 30 days | Mid/High |
| 4 | CISO Fortune 500, zero engagement | Low |
| 5 | Competitor employee, high engagement | Excluded |
| 6 | Bounced + opted out + recent physical event | Edge case |
| 7 | Broken conversion link, split engagement | Edge case |
| 8 | 40 campaigns, 38 automated email sends | Mid/Low |
| 9 | Re-MQL'd 4 times over 2 years | Ambiguous |
| 10 | CC contact, high-intent account, 2 form fills | High |

## Reproducibility

All seeds fixed (`Faker.seed(42)`, `random.seed(42)`, `np.random.seed(42)`).
